  "description": "<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://img.wdjimg.com/mms/icon/v1/b/7a/1b7ac6f8826971800db4c448dc1637ab_256_256.png\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p766048\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\tThe plot of the next film could be told as a fairy tale. A storyteller loses the power of sight and is confined to a tower, except the setting is <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/contemporary\" target=\"_blank\">contemporary</a> Oslo and the woman chooses not to leave her apartment. But Blind, which won a <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/screenwriting\" target=\"_blank\">screenwriting</a> award at Sundance last year and took home a prize from Berlin, is an unusual take on a woman in <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/peril\" target=\"_blank\">peril</a> situation. Forget Audrey Hepburn in Wait Until Dark or Joan Allen in Manhunter, this is another kind of blind protagonist. Ingrid may not be able to see, but her imagination can roam. And the director-writer Eskil Vogt takes the audience on a strange, provocative, sometimes sexually explicit journey.</p>\n<p>\n\t&quot;Films are visual, and when you think about it, film only have two senses and if you take away looking, what do you have left like a black screen with sound which would be a cheap film to make, but not many people would see it, I guess. It wasn't until I thought of the difference between being born blind and having been able to see and then losing your sight and then suddenly it became obvious to me that this was very cinematic, that I could do a lot of interesting things with cinema form, because someone who could see before still have visual <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/imagination\" target=\"_blank\">imagination</a>, would constantly imagine her surroundings or if something made a sound, she would be able to see something that produced that sound and the sound would change, and her image would change. And instead of being a life in darkness, it would be a life in darkness with images <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/constantly\" target=\"_blank\">constantly</a> flickering at the speed of thought, and that's like seeing a film in a movie theatre.&quot;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t<span>声明：音视频均来自互联网链接，仅供学习使用。本网站自身不存储、控制、修改被链接的内容。&ldquo;沪江</span><a>英语</a><span>&rdquo;高度重视知识产权保护。当如发现本网站发布的信息包含有侵犯其著作权的链接内容时，请联系我们，我们将依法采取措施移除相关内容或屏蔽相关链接。&gt;&gt;<a href=\"http://class.hujiang.com/course/52569?source=16553\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0,90,148);\" target=\"_blank\">零基础直达流利生活口语班</a>&lt;&lt;</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p766048/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p766048\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772792/\">学习外语：10条质朴而实用的方法</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772880/\">凯特王妃访印之旅：优雅高贵又尽显民族风</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772694/\">囧研究：聪明的人更喜欢独处</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p771638/\">美剧词汇精讲：《美少女的谎言》weird</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772455/\">阿瓦达索命！这次我们的哈利演了一具尸体……</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772590/\">好吃只会说yummy？学学食物百味如何描述</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772930/\">霍金开微博啦！这些名人大腕居然都有微博！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p772718/\">这个印度女子用一台爱心冰箱温暖了一群人……</a></li><li style=